news.title: Government to enforce real estate regulations, strengthen Odisha RERA compliance
news.para: The decision was taken at a high-level meeting chaired by chief secretary Manoj Ahuja recently. As per the decision, authorities have been asked to invoke the Odisha Public Demand Recovery (OPDR) Act to recover penalties from defaulters, ensuring compliance with ORERA's directives.

news.title: Notices to 266 for business operations at homes, building code violations in Gurugram
news.para: Of these, 183 were in phase 3 and 83 in Phase 2. In total, over 650 notices have been issued in the past three weeks. The team led by DTP (enforcement) Amit Madholia conducted a door-to-door survey in Sectors 55, 56, and 57 to identify properties being misused for commercial use.

news.title: Adani Properties gets NCLT nod to acquire HDIL's two assets
news.para: The assets include a commercial property known as 'Inspire BKC' in Mumbai's business district Bandra-Kurla Complex and a land parcel in Kalyan Shahad on the outskirts of Mumbai. Adani Properties was found to be the only bidder to make Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC)-compliant proposal for both the properties.

news.title: Property rates in Lucknow to surge as new circle rates to come into force from Aug 1
news.para: The new rates, reflecting an average increase of 15% across property types, aim to align with the city's rapid urbanization, enhanced infrastructure, and growing property demand, said additional district magistrate (finance), Rakesh Kumar said.

news.title: Jaipur development body to conduct lottery for three residential schemes on July 2
news.para: "The lottery will be held at the Citizen Service Centre of JDA headquarters. We are going to stream the entire event live on JDA's YouTube channel and Facebook page," said JDA commissioner Anandhi in a press statement.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram leads state in residential registrations
news.para: From Jan 1 to June 30, state capital recorded a remarkable 1,068 residential units, the highest in the state and the only district to surpass the 1,000-unit milestone.

news.title: Allahabad HC orders 220 flats’ registry after builder in Noida offers to pay ₹25 crore more
news.para: The order came after the developer agreed to deposit an additional Rs 25 crore with the Authority in two weeks, making 50 more flats eligible for registry.

news.title: CCI orders probe into market abuse charges against Asian Paints
news.para: The direction follows a complaint filed by Grasim Industries (Birla Paints Division), which accused Asian Paints of engaging in exclusionary practices aimed at stifling its entry and growth in the Indian decorative paints segment.

news.title: NTT seeks up to $864 million in data centre REIT's Singapore IPO
news.para: NTT DC REIT's portfolio comprises six data centre assets located in the United States, Austria and Singapore, according to a preliminary prospectus filed on Friday.

news.title: ED raids Raheja Developers in case related to 'fraud' with homebuyers
news.para: The money laundering case of the Enforcement Directorate (ED) stems from multiple FIRs registered by the Economic Offences Wing (EOW) of the Delhi Police against Raheja Developers Ltd, its Managing Director Naveen Raheja and others, the federal agency said in a statement.

news.title: Home prices in Germany rise 3.8% in Q1 2025
news.para: After more than a decade of uninterrupted gains, home prices began to drop in 2022 after the European Central Bank began a rapid increase in interest rates to curb rampant inflation, sparking Germany's worst real estate crisis in decades.

news.title: Haryana digitising land bank module, integrating with India industrial land bank
news.para: Haryana is also pushing ahead with "plug and play" facilities through the development of flatted factories in key locations such as Industrial Model Township Faridabad, IMT Manesar Phase-V, Sohna, Kharkhoda, Karnal, Yamunanagar, and Saha.

news.title: House prices in UK fall 0.8% in June 2025: Nationwide data
news.para: Economists polled by Reuters had forecast a 0.2% monthly increase. For the year, house prices were 2.1% higher than a year ago, below a 3.5% rise in May and lagging a consensus for a 3.1% annual increase.

news.title: Gujarat waives 80% stamp duty on property transfers via allotment letter, share certificates
news.para: Chief Minister Bhupendra Patel on Monday took the decision to grant the relief which has been given under Section 9(a) of the Gujarat Stamp Act, 1958.

news.title: Kalpataru shares make flat market debut; later surges over 9%
news.para: The stock started trading at Rs 414.10 on the BSE. But, it later gathered momentum and climbed 9.42 per cent to Rs 453 against the issue price. At the NSE, the stock got listed at par with the issue price of Rs 414. Later, it surged 9.37 per cent to Rs 452.80 apiece.

news.title: REA India appoints Praveen Sharma as its CEO
news.para: REA Group has named Praveen Sharma as the new CEO of REA India, adding him to their executive leadership team. Sharma, bringing over 25 years of experience from companies like Paytm and Google, will start in July.

news.title: Gujarat waives 80% duty on property transfers sans sale deeds
news.para: The decision, issued by the revenue department under Section 9A of the Gujarat Stamp Act, comes in response to representations made by citizens and elected representatives.

news.title: Over three lakh clear house tax in Q1 FY26 in Lucknow
news.para: The LMC offered a 10% rebate on house tax payments made through online mode until June 30, 2025. With this deadline now over, a revised rebate structure comes into effect from July 1.

news.title: Pune civic body extends property tax discount deadline to July 7
news.para: Property owners should ensure that they pay the tax on time and avoid a last-minute rush," said Avinash Sapkal, head of property tax department of Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC).

news.title: Goa: Green nod for sand mining in Mandovi challenged in NGT
news.para: The group has currently challenged one EC granted on Feb 3, 2025, and informed the tribunal that it would be filing separate appeals against all the remaining 11 ECs as well.
